switchAtmMib.name: switchAtmMib

revisions.description: Changed the status of atmxCipVci to obsolete. Added atmxCipRipMode to atmxCipEntry. Added a new table, atmxCipVciTable. Each ATM CIP may be supported by multiple VCIs. The atmxCipVciEntry links each atmxCipEntry to one or more conceptual rows in the atmxCipVciTable. Revised the descripiton of atmxCipRowStatus to include the dependancy of atmxCipVciRowStatus. See also the description of atmCipVciRowStatus for details of the relationship. Added atmxCipArpSource and atmxCipArpRowStatus to the atmxCipArpTable and atmxLecArpSource and atmxLecArpRowStatus to the atmxLecArpTable to allow managment to create and delete entries in these tables. Added the tables atmxPtToPtTable, atmxTrunkTable, atmxTrunkVlanTable. Added the object atmxLecVlanNumber to the atmxLecTable. Changed the status of atmxLecUnicastMacAddress to obsolete. Added the object atmxPortSignalingMode to the atmxPortTable.

switchAtmMib.description: The MIB module for ATM support. This module is designed with the assumption that only one virtual path identifier (VPI) may be assigned and is usually determined by the underlying software implementation. The VPI is never used as an index in any table in this module.

IfIndexOrZero.name: IfIndexOrZero
IfIndexOrZero.description: An extension of InterfacesIndex to include the value 0. The value 0 may be used to indicate instances where 0, unknown, or all interfaces may apply.

AtmVpi.name: AtmVpi
AtmVpi.description: ATM VPI. This is a constant with a value of 0.

AtmClientVci.name: AtmClientVci
AtmClientVci.description: This type restricts VCI values to those not reserved by the ATM Forum.

AtmClearStats.name: AtmClearStats
AtmClearStats.description: Flag to clear the counters to 0. A SNMP Get operation will always return 'noOp'

AtmxArpEntryType.name: AtmxArpEntryType
AtmxArpEntryType.description: Indicates how the ArpEntry was learned or created and whether it is subject to aging other(1) - The entry does not fall into any other category. learnedViaArp(2) - learned from ARP. learnedViaData(3) - learned from observing incoming traffic. staticVolatile(4) - created by management and will not age. It may not survive a system restart. staticNonVolatile(5) - created by management and will not age. It will survive a system restart.

AtmxVlanRange.name: AtmxVlanRange
AtmxVlanRange.description: The range of valid vlan numbers.

atmxPortTable.name: atmxPortTable
atmxPortTable.description: A table of port layer status and parameter information for the UNI's physical interface.

atmxPortEntry.name: atmxPortEntry
atmxPortEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about the physical layer of a UNI interface.

atmxPortIndex.name: atmxPortIndex
atmxPortIndex.description: A unique value which identifies this atm submodule port.

atmxPortDescription.name: atmxPortDescription
atmxPortDescription.description: A description for this atm port.

atmxPortTransmissionType.name: atmxPortTransmissionType
atmxPortTransmissionType.description: The transmission type of this port. For example, for a port using the Sonet STS-3c physical layer at 155.52 Mbs, this object would have the value 'sonetSTS3c'.

atmxPortMediaType.name: atmxPortMediaType
atmxPortMediaType.description: The type of media being used on this port. For example for a port using coaxial cable, the object would have the value 'coaxCable'.

atmxPortOperStatus.name: atmxPortOperStatus
atmxPortOperStatus.description: The operational state (i.e., actual) of this port. The ILMI should not alarm on a physical interface when the value of this object is 'outOfService'. This capability is useful if the equipment is to be disconnected or for troubleshooting purposes. A value of 'loopBack' indicates that loopback is in place.

atmxPortMaxVCCs.name: atmxPortMaxVCCs
atmxPortMaxVCCs.description: The maximum number of VCCs supported on this UNI.

atmxPortMaxVciBits.name: atmxPortMaxVciBits
atmxPortMaxVciBits.description: The number of active VCI bits on this interface.

atmxPortAddress.name: atmxPortAddress
atmxPortAddress.description: The ATM address assigned to this port. The value of this attribute is normally set via the ILMI. If the ILMI Address registration mib, ATM-FORUM-ADDR-REG, is supported and the the value of atmxPortIlmiStatus is 'up' than atmxPortAddress should have a MAX-ACCESS of read-only.

atmxPortSignalingVersion.name: atmxPortSignalingVersion
atmxPortSignalingVersion.description: Version of the ATM forum UNI Signaling.

atmxPortSignalingVci.name: atmxPortSignalingVci
atmxPortSignalingVci.description: Signaling Vci. ATM Forum has defined VPI/VCI as VPI 0, VCI 5 for signaling.

atmxPortILMIVci.name: atmxPortILMIVci
atmxPortILMIVci.description: ILMI Vci. ATM Forum has defined the VPI 0, VCI 16 for ILMI.

atmxPortAdaptorRamSize.name: atmxPortAdaptorRamSize
atmxPortAdaptorRamSize.description: Segmentation and reassembly memory size in bytes.

atmxPortSignalingMode.name: atmxPortSignalingMode
atmxPortSignalingMode.description: If this has the value 'pvc' then signaling, ILMI and ILMI polling will be automatically disabled.

atmxLecTable.name: atmxLecTable
atmxLecTable.description: A table of LEC status and parameter information.

atmxLecEntry.name: atmxLecEntry
atmxLecEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about the indicated LEC.

atmxLecIndex.name: atmxLecIndex
atmxLecIndex.description: A unique value which identifies this LEC entry.

atmxLecServerAddress.name: atmxLecServerAddress
atmxLecServerAddress.description: ATM Address of the LE Configuration Server if the configuration mode is auto; else, the LE Server ATM Address.

atmxLecUnicastMacAddress.name: atmxLecUnicastMacAddress
atmxLecUnicastMacAddress.description: The Local Unicast MAC address for this LEC. This is now obsolete because the information can be obtained from the vport entry identified by atmxLecVPortNumber.

atmxLecMaxUnknownFrameCount.name: atmxLecMaxUnknownFrameCount
atmxLecMaxUnknownFrameCount.description: Maximum number of frames to the BUS for a given unicast LAN destination within the Maximum unknown Frame time.

atmxLecMaxArpRetryCount.name: atmxLecMaxArpRetryCount
atmxLecMaxArpRetryCount.description: Maximum number of times LE_ARP_REQUEST will be retried for a given frame's LAN destination.

atmxLecArpRespTime.name: atmxLecArpRespTime
atmxLecArpRespTime.description: Maximum time in seconds that the LEC expects an LE_ARP_REQUEST/LE_ARP_RESPONSE cycle to take.

atmxLecMaxUnknownFrameTime.name: atmxLecMaxUnknownFrameTime
atmxLecMaxUnknownFrameTime.description: Time period in seconds for the maximum number of frames that can be sent to the BUS for a given LAN destination.

atmxLecControlTimeout.name: atmxLecControlTimeout
atmxLecControlTimeout.description: Time out period in seconds for timing out most request response control frame interations.

atmxLecVccTimeout.name: atmxLecVccTimeout
atmxLecVccTimeout.description: Maximum in-active time period in seconds a data direct VCC will be active before being released. A value of 0 indicates that it will never be release.

atmxLecAgeingTime.name: atmxLecAgeingTime
atmxLecAgeingTime.description: Maximum time in seconds that an LE client will maintain an entry in its LE-ARP cache in the absence of verification.

atmxLecFlushTimeout.name: atmxLecFlushTimeout
atmxLecFlushTimeout.description: Time limit in seconds to wait to receive an LE_FLUSH_RESPONSE after the LE_FLUSH_REQUEST has been sent before taking recovery action.

atmxLecVPortNumber.name: atmxLecVPortNumber
atmxLecVPortNumber.description: The Virtual port number with which this LEC is associated. If the value of this object is 0, then no virtual port has been assigned and the LEC is not active.

atmxLecProtocolState.name: atmxLecProtocolState
atmxLecProtocolState.description: This object contains the LAN emulation protocol state.

atmxLecRowStatus.name: atmxLecRowStatus
atmxLecRowStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete entries. Only the values 'active', 'createAndGo', and 'delete are supported.

atmxLecIfIndex.name: atmxLecIfIndex
atmxLecIfIndex.description: This object contains the ifIndex of the corresponding entry in the ifTable. If no such entry exists or unknown then value of this object is 0.

atmxLecId.name: atmxLecId
atmxLecId.description: A value assigned by the LAN Emulation Service (LES) for the LEC identified by atmLecIndex. The value 0 indicates the LES has not assigned a value.

atmxLecControlDirectVcc.name: atmxLecControlDirectVcc
atmxLecControlDirectVcc.description: The VCC assigned for the Control Direct connection. The value 0 indicates the VCC is not set.

atmxLecControlDistributeVcc.name: atmxLecControlDistributeVcc
atmxLecControlDistributeVcc.description: The VCC assigned for the Control Distribute connection. The value 0 indicates the VCC is not set.

atmxLecMulticastSendVcc.name: atmxLecMulticastSendVcc
atmxLecMulticastSendVcc.description: The VCC assigned for Multicast send. The value 0 indicates the VCC is not set.

atmxLecMulticastForwardVcc.name: atmxLecMulticastForwardVcc
atmxLecMulticastForwardVcc.description: The VCC assigned for multicast forwarding. The value 0 indicates the VCC is not set.

atmxLecVlanNumber.name: atmxLecVlanNumber
atmxLecVlanNumber.description: The virtual LAN number to which this LEC is attached. This object is required for row creation and the value of this object must correspond to an existing vLanNumber object in the 'SWITCH-VLAN-MIB.vLanTable'. After a successful row creation, this value may change as a result of moving the virtual port, atmxLecIfIndex, to a different Vlan.

atmxCipTable.name: atmxCipTable
atmxCipTable.description: A table of CIP status and parameter information.

atmxCipEntry.name: atmxCipEntry
atmxCipEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about the indicated CIP.

atmxCipIndex.name: atmxCipIndex
atmxCipIndex.description: A unique value which identifies this CIP entry.

atmxCipIPAddress.name: atmxCipIPAddress
atmxCipIPAddress.description: The IP address associated with this CIP entity.

atmxCipIPSubnetMask.name: atmxCipIPSubnetMask
atmxCipIPSubnetMask.description: The IP subnet mask associated with this CIP entity.

atmxCipConnectionType.name: atmxCipConnectionType
atmxCipConnectionType.description: The connection type of this CIP. If during row creation the value of this object is 'pvc', then at least one entry in the atmxCipVciTable is required before atmxCipRowStatus can be set to 'active'. If during row creation the value is 'svc' then atmxCipServerAtmAddress must be set before atmxCipRowStatus can be set to 'active'.

atmxCipVci.name: atmxCipVci
atmxCipVci.description: The virtual channel identifier associated with this CIP, if PVC.

atmxCipServerAtmAddress.name: atmxCipServerAtmAddress
atmxCipServerAtmAddress.description: ATM Address of the ARP server for the logical IP subnet, to which this CIP belongs. This object is required if atmxCipConnectionType is 'svc'.

atmxCipMtuSize.name: atmxCipMtuSize
atmxCipMtuSize.description: The maximum size of the transmit or receive SDU size of all connections associated with this CIP entity.

atmxCipIfIndex.name: atmxCipIfIndex
atmxCipIfIndex.description: This value of this object identifies the corresponding entry in the ifTable. If this object has the value of 0 then there is no corresponding entry in the ifTable.

atmxCipProtocolState.name: atmxCipProtocolState
atmxCipProtocolState.description: The state of the CIP Protocol.

atmxCipAdmStatus.name: atmxCipAdmStatus
atmxCipAdmStatus.description: The administrative status of this CIP instance.

atmxCipOperStatus.name: atmxCipOperStatus
atmxCipOperStatus.description: The operational status of this CIP instance.

atmxCipRowStatus.name: atmxCipRowStatus
atmxCipRowStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete atmxCipEntry. To create of a logical row, set this object to 'createAndWait'. Before this object can be set to 'active', the objects atmxCipIPAddress, atmxCipIPSubnetMask, atmxCipConnectionType must be set to the appropriate values and at least one entry must be created in the atmxCipVciTable with the same atmxCipIndex value as used with this object instance. When this object is set to 'active', the logical rows in atmxCipVciTable with the same atmxCipIndex value will also be set to 'active'. If this object is set to 'delete', the logical rows in atmxCipVciTable with the same atmxCipIndex value will also be deleted.

atmxCipRipMode.name: atmxCipRipMode
atmxCipRipMode.description: If the value of this object is 'silent', RIP daemon processes received routing packets and does NOT send routing packets over the interface identified by atmxCipIfIndex. With a value of 'active', RIP sends and receives routing packets. With a value of 'deaf' RIP sends routing packets and does not process recieved packets. With a value of 'inactive' RIP deamon does not send nor receive routing packets.

atmxCipVciTable.name: atmxCipVciTable
atmxCipVciTable.description: A table which contains VCIs associated with each CIP.

atmxCipVciEntry.name: atmxCipVciEntry
atmxCipVciEntry.description: An entry in the table, identifying each VCI for a CIP.

atmxCipVciId.name: atmxCipVciId
atmxCipVciId.description: The virtual channel identifier associated with this CIP.

atmxCipVciRowStatus.name: atmxCipVciRowStatus
atmxCipVciRowStatus.description: This object is used to create and delete entries in the atmxCipVciTable. An object instance of this object corresponds to an object instance of atmxCipRowStatus if both objects have the same for atmxCipIndex index value. There may be multiple instances of this object which correspond to the same instance of atmxCipRowStatus. To create a conceptual row in this table and the corresponding object instance atmxCipRowStatus does not exist or has the value 'notReady', the value for atmxCipVciRowStatus in an SNMP Set operation can be only 'createAndWait'. Under these conditions, atmxCipVciRowStatus cannot be set to 'active' but transitions to 'active' as a side effect of an SNMP set operation changing atmxCipRowStatus to 'active'. At least one corresponding instance of atmxCipVciRowStatus must exist before atmxCipRowStatus can transition to 'active'. To create a conceptual row in this table and the corresponding object instance atmxCipRowStatus exists with the value 'active' then the value for atmxCipVciRowStatus may be 'createAndWait' or 'createAndGo'. An SNMP Set operation may not set the value of this object to 'active' unless the the corresponde atmxCipRowStatus has the value 'active'.

atmxLayerStatsTable.name: atmxLayerStatsTable
atmxLayerStatsTable.description: A table of ATM layer statistics information.

atmxLayerStatsEntry.name: atmxLayerStatsEntry
atmxLayerStatsEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about the ATM layer statistics.

atmxLayerStatsTxCells.name: atmxLayerStatsTxCells
atmxLayerStatsTxCells.description: The total number of successfully transmitted cells.

atmxLayerStatsRxCells.name: atmxLayerStatsRxCells
atmxLayerStatsRxCells.description: The total number of successfully received cells.

atmxLayerStatsTxCellDiscards.name: atmxLayerStatsTxCellDiscards
atmxLayerStatsTxCellDiscards.description: The total number of transmit cells that are discarded.

atmxLayerStatsRxCellDiscards.name: atmxLayerStatsRxCellDiscards
atmxLayerStatsRxCellDiscards.description: The total number of receive cells that are discarded.

atmxLayerStatsClear.name: atmxLayerStatsClear
atmxLayerStatsClear.description: When this attribute is set to 'clearStats', the counters for this logical row are reset to 0 and atmxLayerStatsClearTime is reset to 0.

atmxLayerStatsClearTime.name: atmxLayerStatsClearTime
atmxLayerStatsClearTime.description: Amount of time in seconds that has elapsed since the counters have been cleared.

aal5LayerStatsTable.name: aal5LayerStatsTable
aal5LayerStatsTable.description: A table of AAL5 layer statistics information.

aal5LayerStatsEntry.name: aal5LayerStatsEntry
aal5LayerStatsEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about the AAL5 layer statistics.

aal5LayerTxOctets.name: aal5LayerTxOctets
aal5LayerTxOctets.description: The total number of successfully transmitted octets for all AAL5 connections.

aal5LayerTxCells.name: aal5LayerTxCells
aal5LayerTxCells.description: The total number of successfully transmitted cells for all AAL5 connections.

aal5LayerTxSDUs.name: aal5LayerTxSDUs
aal5LayerTxSDUs.description: The total number of successfully transmitted service data units for all AAL5 connections.

aal5LayerTxSDUDiscards.name: aal5LayerTxSDUDiscards
aal5LayerTxSDUDiscards.description: The total number of transmit SDUs discarded.

aal5LayerTxErrors.name: aal5LayerTxErrors
aal5LayerTxErrors.description: The total number of transmit SDUs that could not be transmitted due to errors.

aal5LayerRxOctets.name: aal5LayerRxOctets
aal5LayerRxOctets.description: The total number of successfully received octets for all AAL5 connections.

aal5LayerRxCells.name: aal5LayerRxCells
aal5LayerRxCells.description: The total number of successfully received cells for all AAL5 connections.

aal5LayerRxSDUs.name: aal5LayerRxSDUs
aal5LayerRxSDUs.description: The total number of successfully received service data units for all AAL5 connections.

aal5LayerRxSDUDiscards.name: aal5LayerRxSDUDiscards
aal5LayerRxSDUDiscards.description: The total number of received SDUs discarded.

aal5LayerRxErrors.name: aal5LayerRxErrors
aal5LayerRxErrors.description: The total number of errored SDUs that received.

aal5LayerRxSarTimeouts.name: aal5LayerRxSarTimeouts
aal5LayerRxSarTimeouts.description: The total number of partially re-assembled SDUs that were discarded.

aal5LayerRxCrcErrors.name: aal5LayerRxCrcErrors
aal5LayerRxCrcErrors.description: The total number of SDUs that were received with CRC errors.

aal5LayerRxSDUInvalidSz.name: aal5LayerRxSDUInvalidSz
aal5LayerRxSDUInvalidSz.description: The total number of SDUs discarded because their size exceeded the max SDU size.

aal5LayerClearStats.name: aal5LayerClearStats
aal5LayerClearStats.description: When this attribute is set to 'clearStats', the counters for this logical row are reset to 0 and aal5LayerStatsClearTime is reset to 0.

aal5LayerStatsClearTime.name: aal5LayerStatsClearTime
aal5LayerStatsClearTime.description: Amount of time in seconds that has elapsed since the counters have been reset.

atmxVccStatsTable.name: atmxVccStatsTable
atmxVccStatsTable.description: A table of ATM virtual channel connection statistics information.

atmxVccStatsEntry.name: atmxVccStatsEntry
atmxVccStatsEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about the ATM virtual channel connection statistics.

atmxVccStatsTxSDUs.name: atmxVccStatsTxSDUs
atmxVccStatsTxSDUs.description: The total number of transmitted SDU's on this virtual channel.

atmxVccStatsTxCells.name: atmxVccStatsTxCells
atmxVccStatsTxCells.description: The total number of transmitted cells on this virtual channel.

atmxVccStatsTxOctets.name: atmxVccStatsTxOctets
atmxVccStatsTxOctets.description: The total number of transmitted octets on this virtual channel.

atmxVccStatsRxSDUs.name: atmxVccStatsRxSDUs
atmxVccStatsRxSDUs.description: The total number of received SDU's on this virtual channel.

atmxVccStatsRxCells.name: atmxVccStatsRxCells
atmxVccStatsRxCells.description: The total number of received cells on this virtual channel.

atmxVccStatsRxOctets.name: atmxVccStatsRxOctets
atmxVccStatsRxOctets.description: The total number of received octets on this virtual channel.

atmxVccStatsTxSDUDiscards.name: atmxVccStatsTxSDUDiscards
atmxVccStatsTxSDUDiscards.description: The total number of transmit SDUs discarded on this virtual channel.

atmxVccStatsTxErrors.name: atmxVccStatsTxErrors
atmxVccStatsTxErrors.description: The total number of transmit SDU errors on this virtual channel.

atmxVccStatsRxSDUDiscards.name: atmxVccStatsRxSDUDiscards
atmxVccStatsRxSDUDiscards.description: The total number of receive SDU's discarded on this virtual channel.

atmxVccStatsRxErrors.name: atmxVccStatsRxErrors
atmxVccStatsRxErrors.description: The total number of receive SDU's with errors on this virtual channel.

atmxVccStatsRxSarTimeouts.name: atmxVccStatsRxSarTimeouts
atmxVccStatsRxSarTimeouts.description: The total number of partially re-assembled SDUs that were discarded.

atmxVccStatsRxCrcErrors.name: atmxVccStatsRxCrcErrors
atmxVccStatsRxCrcErrors.description: The total number of receive SDU's crc errors on this virtual channel.

atmxVccStatsRxOversizedSdus.name: atmxVccStatsRxOversizedSdus
atmxVccStatsRxOversizedSdus.description: The total number of receive SDU's that are oversized.

atmxVccStatsConnCreateTime.name: atmxVccStatsConnCreateTime
atmxVccStatsConnCreateTime.description: Time elapsed in seconds since the connection has been created.

atmxVccStatsConnInIdleTime.name: atmxVccStatsConnInIdleTime
atmxVccStatsConnInIdleTime.description: Time that has elapsed in seconds since any traffic has been received on this connection.

atmxVccStatsConnOutIdleTime.name: atmxVccStatsConnOutIdleTime
atmxVccStatsConnOutIdleTime.description: Time that has elapsed in seconds since any traffic has been sent out on this connection.

atmxVccStatsConnModifiedTime.name: atmxVccStatsConnModifiedTime
atmxVccStatsConnModifiedTime.description: Time that has elapsed in seconds since any connection parameters have been modified.

atmxLecStatsTable.name: atmxLecStatsTable
atmxLecStatsTable.description: A table of ATM LEC statistics information.

atmxLecStatsEntry.name: atmxLecStatsEntry
atmxLecStatsEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about the LEC statistics.

atmxLecStatsTxArpReq.name: atmxLecStatsTxArpReq
atmxLecStatsTxArpReq.description: Total number of ARP requests transmitted from this LEC.

atmxLecStatsTxArpRsp.name: atmxLecStatsTxArpRsp
atmxLecStatsTxArpRsp.description: Total number of ARP responses transmitted from this LEC.

atmxLecStatsTxControlPkts.name: atmxLecStatsTxControlPkts
atmxLecStatsTxControlPkts.description: Total number of control packets transmitted from this LEC.

atmxLecStatsTxUnicastPkts.name: atmxLecStatsTxUnicastPkts
atmxLecStatsTxUnicastPkts.description: Total number of unicast packets transmitted from this LEC.

atmxLecStatsTxMulticastPkts.name: atmxLecStatsTxMulticastPkts
atmxLecStatsTxMulticastPkts.description: Total number of multicast packets transmitted from this LEC.

atmxLecStatsTxBroadcastPkts.name: atmxLecStatsTxBroadcastPkts
atmxLecStatsTxBroadcastPkts.description: Total number of broadcast packets transmitted from this LEC.

atmxLecStatsTxDiscardPkts.name: atmxLecStatsTxDiscardPkts
atmxLecStatsTxDiscardPkts.description: Total number of transmission packets discarded from this LEC.

atmxLecStatsRxArpReq.name: atmxLecStatsRxArpReq
atmxLecStatsRxArpReq.description: Total number of ARP requests received for this LEC.

atmxLecStatsRxArpRsp.name: atmxLecStatsRxArpRsp
atmxLecStatsRxArpRsp.description: Total number of ARP responses received for this LEC.

atmxLecStatsRxControlPkts.name: atmxLecStatsRxControlPkts
atmxLecStatsRxControlPkts.description: Total number of control packets received for this LEC.

atmxLecStatsRxUnicastPkts.name: atmxLecStatsRxUnicastPkts
atmxLecStatsRxUnicastPkts.description: Total number of unicast packets received for this LEC.

atmxLecStatsRxMulticastPkts.name: atmxLecStatsRxMulticastPkts
atmxLecStatsRxMulticastPkts.description: Total number of multicast packets received for this LEC.

atmxLecStatsRxBroadcastPkts.name: atmxLecStatsRxBroadcastPkts
atmxLecStatsRxBroadcastPkts.description: Total number of broadcast packets received for this LEC.

atmxLecStatsRxDiscardPkts.name: atmxLecStatsRxDiscardPkts
atmxLecStatsRxDiscardPkts.description: Total number of discarded packets received for this LEC.

atmxCipStatsTable.name: atmxCipStatsTable
atmxCipStatsTable.description: A table of ATM CIP statistics information.

atmxCipStatsEntry.name: atmxCipStatsEntry
atmxCipStatsEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing information about the CIP statistics.

atmxCipStatsPktsFromOtherLIS.name: atmxCipStatsPktsFromOtherLIS
atmxCipStatsPktsFromOtherLIS.description: Total number of packets received that does not belong to this logical IP subnet.

atmxCipStatsTxArpReq.name: atmxCipStatsTxArpReq
atmxCipStatsTxArpReq.description: Total number of ARP requests transmitted from this CIP.

atmxCipStatsTxArpRsp.name: atmxCipStatsTxArpRsp

atmxCipStatsTxInArpReq.name: atmxCipStatsTxInArpReq
atmxCipStatsTxInArpReq.description: Total number of InARP requests transmitted from this CIP.

atmxCipStatsTxInArpRsp.name: atmxCipStatsTxInArpRsp
atmxCipStatsTxInArpRsp.description: Total number of InARP responses transmitted from this CIP.

atmxCipStatsTxDiscards.name: atmxCipStatsTxDiscards

atmxCipStatsRxArpReq.name: atmxCipStatsRxArpReq
atmxCipStatsRxArpReq.description: Total number of ARP requests received for this CIP.

atmxCipStatsRxArpRsp.description: Total number of ARP responses received for this CIP.

atmxCipStatsRxInArpReq.name: atmxCipStatsRxInArpReq
atmxCipStatsRxInArpReq.description: Total number of InARP requests received for this CIP.

atmxCipStatsRxInArpRsp.name: atmxCipStatsRxInArpRsp

atmxCipStatsRxDiscards.name: atmxCipStatsRxDiscards
atmxCipStatsRxDiscards.description: Total number of packets discarded on receive for this CIP.

atmxSscopStatsTxDiscardSdus.name: atmxSscopStatsTxDiscardSdus
atmxSscopStatsTxDiscardSdus.description: Total number of transmit SDUs discarded by SSCOP.

atmxSscopStatsTxDiscardPdus.name: atmxSscopStatsTxDiscardPdus
atmxSscopStatsTxDiscardPdus.description: Total number of transmit PDUs discarded by SSCOP.

atmxSscopStatsTxErrorPdus.name: atmxSscopStatsTxErrorPdus
atmxSscopStatsTxErrorPdus.description: Total number of transmit PDUs with transmission errors.
